post_text:
Good afternoon,

This is Mr. Carrubba, Superintendent of the Belvidere School District.
This afternoon, Governor Murphy and Commissioner Repollet announced that we will be returning to in person learning in September. I anticipate reviewing the plan from the Department of Education shortly. The district has been working on a plan for reopening, some of which is highlighted on our website, and we are committed to having our plan in place as soon as practicable.
I will be keep everyone updated as we move through this process and would like to ensure everyone that the health of our students and staff is paramount to our plan.
Please enjoy your weekend and stay healthy.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

This is Mr. Carrubba of the Belvidere School District. I wanted to take a moment this afternoon to update and remind everyone of our end of the school year dates.

The last official day for school for this calendar year is June the 9th. Any information on the returning materials to the schools will be forthcoming.

This weeks update by Governor Murphy on graduations will allow us to hold in-person graduations for our BHS seniors as well as our BES 8th graders. Our plan is to hold our BHS graduation on July 8th at 10 am and our 8th grade graduation on July 9th at 5:30 pm. More information on both ceremonies will be released once we have further guidance from the department of Education.

At this point we are also working on our re-opening plan for the upcoming school year, and hope to release the plan in the early part of July.

I want to thank everyone for the patience and endurance during this difficult time. This has certainly been a school year like no other, and I am proud to say that we all come together to finish the year strong.

Stay healthy.

post_text: Seater Spotlight: Senior Deme Nikolopoulos is working toward her Gold Award, the highest award a Girl Scout can earn! For her project, she is providing elementary environmental education to students in White Twp., Belvidere, Harmony and Hope by creating a program that will provide a series of monthly education videos, activities and worksheets, and contests. Each month will focus on a different environmental issue and the program will teach our K-8 students about what they can do to help save our planet! Please help her out by encouraging your children and family to participate in these activities and contests! Information can be found on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook by searching @gogreenandgold2020.

post_text:
The BHS Drama Club Cast of Beauty & the Beast presents "Human Again" on YouTube: https://youtu.be/nsd9kZ3Cq-g

After seeing virtual performances from professional productions and high schools in our area, many of us thought that this would be a great opportunity for our cast to be able to sing together again. When we were thinking about what song we were going to sing, Human Again was the obvious choice. Much like the characters in Beauty and the Beast, we all can relate to not feeling quite like ourselves, and not being able to do what we are used to. We are looking forward to the day where we can be dancing together again soon. Until that day comes, please enjoy Human Again, performed by the cast of Belvidere High School's production of Beauty and the Beast!

post_text: Good Morning Belvidere School District families! There will be a change in the pickup schedule for free/reduced lunch students. In an effort to minimize the number of times you have to come to the school, the food will now be available for pickup on Mondays and Thursdays. We will still distribute from the BHS gym entrance from 8:30 to 10:00 am. We will ensure that you have enough food to last for the amount of time between pickups. This will go into effect beginning on Monday, March 30, 2020. In addition, Oxford Street families can also report to the gym lobby entrance to pick up packets of work on Mondays and Thursdays as well. Thank you for your assistance and your understanding!

post_text: The March 18, 2020 BOE meeting tomorrow will go on as scheduled at 7 p.m. Given the current situation with the CoronaVirus, we are asking the public to participate in a "virtual" meeting. The meeting will be live streamed as normal and the public can participate via email to the Board Secretary at rtjalma@belvideresd.org. Emails will be accepted between the start of the meeting at 7 p.m. until we begin the second Public Participation. The emailed comments from the public will be read during the two Public Participations. Some BOE members will be in attendance, while others will be participating remotely. The BOE has been advised to hold this previously scheduled meeting in order to approve the preliminary 2020-21 budget that is due this week.

post_text:
Good evening,

This is Mr. Carrubba of the Belvidere School District. I wanted to take a moment to give everyone a quick schedule update. On Monday March 16th the Belvidere School District will operate on an early dismissal schedule for students only. We will be using the time in the afternoon for staff planning. While we feel that it is highly unlikely that we would have to shut the district down in case of an outbreak of CoronaVirus, we feel that it is important to have a plan in place in case of the unlikely scenario.

We will be providing aftercare at Belvidere Elementary from 12:20-2:25 for parents who will be unable to make arrangements for their children. We do ask that you please update the Parent Portal if you do need to take advantage of the aftercare for Monday or contact the main office of your school.

The situation with the CoronaVirus is a fluid one, and we will continue to update everyone as more information becomes available.

Have a great evening.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

This afternoon during recess, a rifle casing was found in the playground mulch at Oxford Street School. The Belvidere Police Department was contacted immediately and an investigation ensued. It was determined by the police that due to weathering it had not been fired recently, and after later inspection it was identified as a "blank" ammunition round. The police determined that this was not a threat to our school's safety.

All necessary precautions were taken, and at no point was the safety of our students and staff at risk.

Thank you and have a great afternoon.
text:
Good afternoon,

This afternoon during recess, a rifle casing was found in the playground mulch at Oxford Street School. The Belvidere Police Department was contacted immediately and an investigation ensued. It was determined by the police that due to weathering it had not been fired recently, and after later inspection it was identified as a "blank" ammunition round. The police determined that this was not a threat to our school's safety.

All necessary precautions were taken, and at no point was the safety of our students and staff at risk.

Thank you and have a great afternoon.

Middle School students are permitted to wear school appropriate costumes and can watch the parade from the bleachers.

The 9th annual Peggy's Run, a 5K or 1 mile Run/Walk will be held on Saturday, June 8 at 9 am-beginning on the Belvidere High School Track. Peggy's Run is the main fundraiser for the Peggy Zetterstrom Memorial Music Scholarship given to graduating seniors. Over $56,000 has been given out over the last 15 years. Registration will begin at 8 am and the event is rain or shine.
Folks can sign up the day of the race or click the link below to sign up:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfoVwwLQaD_Riz3ZhnHsfAsEItEJqkyUEQdUUnGA-EJjbq6gg/viewform

Thank you all in advance for supporting this event.

post_text: Principal's Forum: Monday, May 20, 2019 at 6:00pm in the Oxford Street Media Center for all parents of students in grades PreK-8. Discussion items will include transition details for Third Street students, 2019-20 school year Pick Up & Drop Off procedures, introducing the new Director of the Child Study Team and a Q&A session.

post_text:
Good evening,

Just a reminder that the Belvidere School District will operate on an early dismissal schedule, tomorrow, Thursday April 19th. The School district will also be closed for Spring Break from April 19th-28th and will reopen on Monday, April 29th.

A reminder that the Board of Education meeting that was scheduled for Wednesday, May 8th has been moved to Monday, May 6th at 7 PM in the BHS Media Center. Our annual budget presentation will take place that evening.

We are looking for volunteers to help establish our Belvidere Education Foundation. We are hoping that community members and alumni will be interested in helping us to get this venture up and running. If you have any interest, please contact the Board of Education office at 475-6000 for more information.

Have a great break!

post_text: Registration for FREE PreSchool is going on now for children ages 3 & 4 years old living in Belvidere! Only a limited number of spots are available so reserve yours today by visiting the Oxford Street Website under the Our School tab labelled Student Registration Information.
